def: Existing in the mind, but below the surface or threshold ofconsciousness; that is, existing as feeling rather than as clearideas.
A bullying and violent person; a braggart; a swashbuckler.[Obs.]That flock of stout, bragging rushbucklers. Robynson (More's Utopia).
Dead pay; the crime of taking pay for the service of deadsoldiers, or for services not actually rendered by soldiers. [Obs.]Bacon.
That which beats or throbs in working.
To lie or act as a mountaineer; to climb mountains.You can't go mountaineering in a flat country. H. James.
One of the order of Coleoptera.
